rComments: The expectations in ENG266 were very unclear. Tests are graded unfairly - in comparison with the rest of the students. Those with background knowledge of other languages are favoured and given an unfair advantage.

He is SO nice and he actually wants his students to be successful which is rare these days. He is always willing to help you get the best mark and he bellcurves like crazy which is awesome. He'll occasionally say something weird/random to the class like how sexy he finds poetry (lol) but his passion is truely unmatched.. GREAT PROF.
Prof. Randy is great. He doesn't limit your creativity with essay structures. Easy to talk to. Very helpful. Tests are simple if you understand. If you don't ask him, he'll help you out.

"Randy" is amazing! He is an incredibly smart man and probably the most reasonable and kind professor I've ever had. He will literally go far out of his way to help you. I had never taken english before but now would again as long as he was the prof. I will never look at the english language the same way again.

I'll always be grateful for the second and third chances given to me by Randy. It's true that you need to be intelligent to get the most out of his class, as it is pretty free-form, and you'll have to contribute in order to keep things moving and lively. Extremely knowledgeable in his field, and shows this if you set him up. Very open and kind.

Professor McLeod is somewhat unclear in his expectations and his lectures have absolutely no structure. He seems to just wing it because he knows the content so well. He is very helpful, though, if you are willing to devote extra time to meeting him one on one during his office hours. His classes are for really intelligent people.
A very confusing and slightly unprofessional professor. His is the only class I have ever dropped because of a poor teaching style that grated on my nerves.
What can I say, he's soo helpful its unbelievable, very fun class
